The following instructions for debugging Micro-Manager with Netbeans are intended to work on Windows or Mac.

<ol>
<li>Download and install Micro-Manager.</li>
<li>Download a copy of the latest Micro-Manager [http://micro-manager.org/downloads.php?object=source source] (1.3 or 1.4) using [http://subversion.apache.org/ subversion].</li>
<li>Download, install and run [http://netbeans.org Netbeans].</li>
<li>Select '''File'''...'''Open Project...''', and choose <your_micromanager_code_root>/IDE_projects/NetBeansProjects/mm</li>
<li>Right-click the '''mm''' project (probably at left) and select '''Properties'''.</li>
<li>Select '''Run''' under '''Categories'''</li>
<li>Click "New..." and create a configuration named '''imagej'''.</li>
<li>Set the following parameters: <ul><li>'''Main Class:'''  <code>ij.ImageJ</code></li>
<li>'''Working Directory:''' <code><your_micromanager_installation_directory></code></li>
<li>'''VM options:''' <code>-Xmx600M</code>.</li></ul>
<li>Click '''OK''' and select the menu item '''Debug'''...'''Debug Project (mm)'''.
</li>

If all is well, then Micro-Manager should launch inside ImageJ.
</ol>
